$interpreted: Beyata: Did the client get lost? Oh no, this guesthouse is so large, too, where could he have gone?
Beyata: ...I was told his name is Mr. Orisuke, and he'll be wearing blue clothing, he should be easy to spot...
Obsessed Guest: Well, if it isn't Bluebird from the One-Hundred Lillies Guesthouse~ What's the rush, darlin'?
Lovestriken Guest: Why don't you keep us company for a while?
Beyata: Ah... I'm flattered that you would request my company.
Beyata: It's just...
Beyata: I would hate to think you're both abandoning the other girls, the ones you picked in the first place.
Beyata: Thinking of them all alone... why, I just get so sad... I almost want to cry.
Obsessed Guest: ─P-Please don't cry, Bluebird! We're sorry!!
Beyata: Then would you please head back to the other girls, for me~? Why, that would just make me so happy!
Beyata: (That wasted too much time... I have to find Mr. Orisuke, he must be so distraught!)
Beyata: (That man, he seems to be dressed as they described.)
Beyata: Are you... Master Orisuke? I was so worried you had gotten lost~
Orisuke: Ah... B-Bluebird?
Orisuke: I'm sorry, this is my first time here and I got lost! Thank you for coming to find me.
Beyata: It is my pleasure to be of assistance.
Beyata: Now, if you would please come with me~
Merchant: Aw man, I was really hopin' I'd be able to get a glimpse of your top girl. Kind of takes the wind outta my "sales"...
Guesthouse Boss: ...Our top girl? You mean Bluebird?
Beyata: (Is that the boss I hear? And he's talking about me?)
Merchant: Yep~ Funny to think she's still workin' here even though her grandfather is back on his feet again.
Guesthouse Boss: Gyahahaha, don't you worry about that!
Guesthouse Boss: When a woman is sold to Hot Spring Street, she cuts all ties with family! I'd never let her go back home!
Beyata: (...Huh?)
Guesthouse Boss: I just have to dangle some hope in front of them every once in a while, you know?
Merchant: As long as they think they'll go home one day, they'll do anything I say!
Guesthouse Boss: And when it's someone as good as Bluebird, I've got to pull out all the stops. I've written so many letters my hand's about to fall off.
Orisuke: L-Letters? What does he...?
Beyata: (Has he been forging letters in my grandfather's name? Ah... he must be doing that because he cares about me!)
Merchant: ...If one day she realizes her grandpa sold her off, took the money and ran, she'd be so sad she'd never work again!
Guesthouse Boss: But it's alright, I've got a good thing going with her. She'll never figure it out.
Guesthouse Boss: Anyway, enough about Bluebird. What about that Tonic of Rebirth you promised me?
Beyata: ...Took the money and ran? What does he mean? My grandfather is too sick to go anywhere...
Beyata: Do you know what he means, Master Orisuke?
Orisuke: Ah, B-Bluebird, maybe we should go somewhere else! If we're caught eavesdropping, then...
Cruel Staff: What are you two doing loitering around here?
Orisuke: Oh, crap... Ah, we...
Orisuke: Here, a gift for you... on me!
Orisuke: I was simply lost, so lost this little lady here had to come find me! Please don't speak of this to anyone else, I'd be so embarrassed...
Cruel Staff: Yes, of course... You two were in your room the whole time, you didn't see anything~
Orisuke: Bluebird, how about we head to the bath?
Beyata: Yes, Mr. Orisuke...
Orisuke: I'm sure that was hard for you to hear, Bluebird... If you want, I can leave and come back another time...
Orisuke: M-Maybe your grandfather just left to take care of some business, and he's still going to come back for you. Don't lose hope...
Beyata: ...You're very kind, Mr. Orisuke.
Beyata: ...But I heard it from the boss, loud and clear. My grandfather sold me, then took the money and disappeared.
Beyata: My grandfather... betrayed me.
Beyata: The boss isn't the same. He took me in when no one wanted me, he's taken care of me... and he needs me!
Beyata: And you, too, Mr. Orisuke. You've been so nice to me~
Beyata: Everything is fine. As long as I'm still needed, then I am fine~
Beyata: Actually, I'm more than fine! Everything is like a dream!
Orisuke: A dream? B-But, your boss has been lying to you all this time...
Beyata: ─He wasn't lying!!
Beyata: Yaagh, I'm sorry! I-I mean, he might have withheld some of the truth from me... but he was just trying to protect me.
Beyata: That's more than I could have hoped for, since I'm a cursed, wretched girl who doesn't deserve happiness...
Orisuke: ...Bluebird...
Orisuke: You know, when I was selling my cloth, one of my customers told me of you. He said there were legends of you...
Orisuke: The legends said your feathers could bring people happiness.
Beyata: There are legends about me? And they say I make people... happy?
Beyata: That's impossible... I don't believe it...
Orisuke: You just ran into some bad luck, but you're not "cursed". It's like how I can't help but eat a bit too much, and others laugh at me for it...
Orisuke: But I still have self worth, I'm not useless! Don't be so down on yourself!
Beyata: Mr. Orisuke, you... you're the first person to tell me that I make others happy.
Beyata: But... I don't think I have what it takes to be as brave as you.
Orisuke: What do you mean!? Of course you can! And with me here, you don't have anything to worry about!
Beyata: D-Do you mean... you're going to take me away from this place?
Orisuke: ...Eh? N-No, I just─
Orisuke: I mean... maybe if I get that contract with the arbiter next month, then I might be able to make enough money to buy your freedom, but...
Beyata: You're not lying to me, are you?
Orisuke: I mean, I can't promise─
Orisuke: I, I mean, no I'm not lying! I promise I will take you away from Hot Spring Street!
Orisuke: You can trust me, Bluebird. And you don't have to pretend around me, anymore, you can be yourself.
Beyata: Oh, thank you, Mr. Orisuke! You've made me so happy, I don't have any reason to be sad any─
Beyata: ─Ah... Wah... I'm sorry─I lied! I lied!! Waaaaaaaaaaah~
